{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb0b4408-f283-4d72-aae8-d9c98521a4b8","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**What changed (after the `--` separator):**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test projects):\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\n**Project file:** enable the bridge so `dotnet test` forwards to the new platform:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side (before `--`) — it's handled natively by both runners.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"44266301-0da0-475c-9643-2f29f7096313","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I can answer this directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me break down their current command and map each part to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalent:\n\n1. `dotnet test` → `dotnet test` (still works, but the underlying runner changes)\n2. `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` → `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` (same syntax works)\n3. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (new flag)\n\n\n4. For code coverage, `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` maps to either the same syntax or the newer `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` flags depending on which coverage tool is being used\n5. The blame-related flags change: `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`, `--blame-hang` becomes `--hangdump`, and `--blame-hang-timeout` becomes `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nThe main shift with Microsoft.Testing.Platform is that the command-line interface has been redesigned, so while some flags remain the same, others have been renamed for clarity and consistency. , which are then interpreted by the test platform. So the TRX output gets enabled with `--report-trx`, and code coverage uses the new `--coverage` syntax with format options. When you invoke `dotnet test` on a Microsoft.Testing.Platform project, arguments after `--` get passed through to the test runner itself.\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically, you'd need to enable the testing platform support explicitly by adding the NuGet package and setting the project property to allow `dotnet test` to recognize the new command-line format. Setting up the property correctly with `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` lets `dotnet test` work directly. The command-line arguments map over from the old `dotnet test` syntax to the new platform equivalents—`--filter` stays the same, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`, and `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump`—though each of these features requires its corresponding extension package installed.\n\nFor `--blame-hang` with a timeout, that translates to `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` using the HangDump package. I'm realizing that `--filter` can stay at the `dotnet test` level rather than after the `--` separator, so the full command would pass the filter directly to `dotnet test` while the platform-specific reporting and diagnostic options go after the `--`.","outputTokens":1951,"requestId":"4817:99ACC:321E301:36B79B0:69FBE3AE"},"id":"307449d2-2465-4fdb-8720-98ef59809d27","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:58:55.710Z","parentId":"29ecdbd8-8898-4c74-8a84-5a38edf6e0b7"}
